'''Reinhard Brandt''' (born 10 April 1937 in [[Klein Gladebrügge]]) is a [[Germany|German]] [[philosophy|philosopher]].

Brandt studied [[Greek language|Greek]], [[Latin]] and philosophy in [[Marburg]], [[Munich]] and [[Paris]]. In 1965 he completed his doctorate on the [[Aristotle|Aristotelian]] theory of judgement. His [[habilitation]] was on an unpublished work of [[David Hume]]'s theoretical philosophy.

From 1972, Brandt was a [[professor]] of [[history of philosophy]] at the [[University of Marburg]]. He retired in 2003. He also taught at several other universities.

His research focus is the philosophy of [[Immanuel Kant]]. He has recently published several articles on Kant in [[Italian language|Italian]].

